# Minikube - Local Kubernetes
Minikube is a tool that enables running a Kubernetes cluster locally for development and testing. It creates a single-node cluster within a virtual machine or a container.

## Minikube Installation
```bash
# Download Minikube
curl -LO https://storage.googleapis.com/minikube/releases/latest/minikube-linux-amd64

# Install
sudo install minikube-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/minikube

# Check installation
minikube version

# Install kubectl (Kubernetes CLI)
curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -L -s https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl"
sudo install -o root -g root -m 0755 kubectl /usr/local/bin/kubectl

# Check kubectl
kubectl version --client
```  
## Minikube Startup
Cluster Startup
```bash
# Start Minikube (uses the Docker driver)
minikube start

# Add usr to docker(when fail to start)
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER

# Refresh usr group
newgrp docker

# test 
docker ps

# Start with a specific driver
minikube start --driver=docker

# Start with more resources
minikube start --cpus=4 --memory=8192

# Check cluster status
minikube status

# Show cluster info
kubectl cluster-info

# Show nodes
kubectl get nodes

# Open Kubernetes Dashboard
minikube dashboard

# Stop Minikube
minikube stop

# Delete cluster
minikube delete

Tip: Minikube requires virtualization support (VT-x/AMD-v) or Docker containers. Ensure they are enabled/in use.
curl -LO https://storage.googleapis.com/minikube/releases/latest/minikube-linux-amd64
```